<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 27 at 5:15PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northeastern Hill
County through 545 PM MDT...
At 514 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Beaver Creek, or 10 miles northwest of Havre, moving northeast at 15
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph, pea size hail and brief heavy
downpours.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Havre, Beaver Creek, and Simpson.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
